column5: Due to my winter use of batteries, I purchase new 12v deep cycle batteries every two seasons.  I'm due to purchase two new batteries this winter, so I have 2 Interstate SRM29 Deep Cycle 12v batteries *free* if anyone would like to pick them up.  I'm in Hamilton, but work in Mississauga.  Because I do frequently update my deep cycle batteries, these are only a few years old. I'll keep my current ones as backup to the two new ones, however, I don't need my current backup set.  They are kept charged at all times.  They likely are at about 70%-75% capacity,compared to a new battery.  Reply here or Msg me.
I could use one of these if moe above me doesn't take both of them
That's very generous of you Steve. Thank you on the community's behalf.
Good thoughts and best wishes Steve, thanks for being a Santa Claus.   Art
Moemoe made first reply so they are going to go to him.  Have a great evening all.  (glad to be able to help out ... much better than sending them to the trash)
or the 10.00 scrappers will pay for them each...... I hope they wind up in a boat. and not a scrap yard.  Good on you Steve!  G
